--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Plastic Metal
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Be a real life Guitar Hero!

Plug in a guitar hero controller and run the script. Plastic Metal will turn
your button presses into synthesized power chords using sox.

---------------------------------------
Installation
---------------------------------------

Plastic Metal requires:
    * Sox ( http://sox.sourceforge.net/ )
    * Pygame ( http://pygame.org/news.html )
    * Xboxdrv ( http://pingus.seul.org/~grumbel/xboxdrv/ or https://github.com/Grumbel/xboxdrv )

You should be able to install Sox and Pygame with your linux distro's
package manager. On debian and ubuntu, you can install both with:

    $ sudo apt-get install sox python-pygame

See xboxdrv's README file for it's installation instructions.


---------------------------------------
Running
---------------------------------------

Plug in your guitar and run these two commands:

    $ sudo xboxdrv --guitar --ui-buttonmap green=JS_0,red=JS_1,yellow=JS_2,blue=JS_3,orange=JS_4,du=JS_5,dd=JS_5 --ui-axismap X2=JS_6:0:-1 -l 6
    $ ./plasticmetal.py


---------------------------------------
Usage
---------------------------------------

By default, the script maps button presses to power chords. Strum without
holding any frets to play an open E power chord. Hold down the green button
to play a power chord one half step above E.

Here's a list of all the power chords you can play currently:

GRYBO
----- Open E power chord
o---- Power chord on the first fret of the E string
-o--- Power chord on the second fret of the E string
--o-- 3
---o- 4
----o 5
oo--- 6
-oo-- 7
--oo- 8
---oo 9
o-o-- 10
-o-o- 11
--o-o 12
ooo-- 13
-ooo- 14
--ooo 15

Holding the whammy bar all the way down whilst playing will play just root notes
rather than power chords.


